#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Flooding and heavy rains are wreaking havoc in KwaZulu-Natal. At least ten people are missing and two people died over the weekend in KwaMashu and Umlazi as a result of the floods. READ: SAWS warns of heavy rains in most of the provinces over the weekend Teams from eThekwini Emergency Services are already on the ground assessing the impact. Watch the video above for more details on this story. At least two people have died and 10 missing in KwaMashu and Umlazi as a result of the floods. Heavy rains are wreaking havoc in KwaZulu Natal. eNCA's Dasen Thathiahhas the latest update. Courtesy #DStv403